TopicTitle: [1.12.x] Parallax - PBR Terrain and Surface Objects [2.0.7]

Articles.Content:
7 minutes ago, Gameslinx said:

Pretty much. Set it to Vertex mode for the best performance but it's best to just not use it altogether

Thx for the quick response!

8 minutes ago, Gameslinx said:

Make sure your terrain shader quality is set to ultra in the game settings

So if you don't set it to ultra there will be no tessellation?

So "Changing your terrain shader quality in the settings now changes your Parallax shader quality" means you can change the shader quality (quite necessary on my potato, which is why I was very happy to read "Added low and medium quality shaders. If you have a slower PC, you'll get good performance from these!"), but there will be no tesselation, or am I getting this all wrong?

2 minutes ago, modus said:

So if you don't set it to ultra there will be no tessellation?

Correct. Tessellation is only possible on Ultra because it's what uses the most performance in the shader. The other variants (Medium and Low) don't use tessellation so that they support older graphics cards or provide a higher framerate
Perfectly clear, thx again!

I've seen other report the same issue, but I've posted it in Github anyways.
I've followed all the steps, I updated to the latest scatterer and set useDepthBufferMode = False
I am using KSP version 1.12.0

https://github.com/Gameslinx/Tessellation/issues/63
How do you enable or disable the physics? I am not getting any.

7 minutes ago, Agustin said:

How do you enable or disable the physics? I am not getting any.

I temporarily removed the collisions because they were causing trouble and I'm in the middle of rewriting it. Because the details are so much smaller, the lack of collisions shouldn't be that noticeable for the time being

23 minutes ago, SpaceXEnthusiast said:

I've followed all the steps, I updated to the latest scatterer and set useDepthBufferMode = False

You need to set it to true
Oh okay I understand. Its good to know you are not abandoning it though because it was very fun on previous version.

I installed the last version (1.3.0), but the mod says that is not compatible with my game version (1.12.1).

Thanks.

16 hours ago, Apolio said:

I reinstalled the latest Scatter and set useDepthBufferMode= True but Eve city lights are still flickering. Unless i was supposed to change it outside the scatter configs

City lights apply a material on top of the terrain. This might cause flickering regardless. Can you install EVE-Redux, if you haven't already, and see if that fixes it? https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/196411-19-112-eve-redux-performance-enhanced-eve-maintenance-v11131-18062021/
